peopleAlsoAsk.question: How to identify the age of a picture frame?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Take note of joint construction – dovetails and mortise-and-tenon joints were common in older frames, while modern frames often feature staples or machine-cut joints. The patina of the frame's finish can also provide insights into its age, as genuine aging often results in a unique, time-worn appearance.
